        "setup": "Register an OAuth client with Day AI, then authorize it for a workspace. The easiest documented path is the Day AI SDK flow: clone [day-ai/day-ai-sdk](https://github.com/day-ai/day-ai-sdk), copy [.env.example](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/day-ai/day-ai-sdk/master/.env.example) to `.env`, set `INTEGRATION_NAME`, then run `yarn oauth:setup`. The README says this registers your OAuth client, opens a browser for authorization, and saves `CLIENT_ID`, `CLIENT_SECRET`, and `REFRESH_TOKEN` to `.env`. The detected OAuth endpoints are authorization at `https://day.ai/integrations/authorize`, token at `https://day.ai/api/oauth`, and dynamic client registration at `https://day.ai/api/oauth/register`. Cataloged scopes include `native_organization:write`, `native_contact:write`, and `assistant:*:use`.",
